<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,907,1367]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,907,932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Occipital carina absent, labrum concealed by clypeus when mandibles closed, notauli and midpit absent, propodeum with strong median carina, hind tibia with no basal carina, apex and base of posterior tibiae black or yellow, wings infumate, stigma broad, fore wing with (RS+M)b present, 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1071,1087,979,993]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">nd</superScript>
submarginal cell long 4-sided, hind wing with m-cu absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,907,1367]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1054,1079]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gahan" authorityYear="1930" box="[346,491,1054,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Opius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis box="[346,491,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Opius bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Wharton" authorityName="Wharton" authorityYear="1997" box="[793,1011,1054,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Bellopius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[793,899,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Bellopius</emphasis>
Wharton
</taxonomicName>
, which is constituted of Neotropical species associated with tephritids, and it is characterized by the absence of the occipital carina and notauli (
<bibRefCitation author="Wharton, R. A." box="[158,325,1126,1151]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 53" refId="ref9687" refString="Wharton, R. A. (1997) Generic relationships of Opiinae Braconidae (Hymenoptera) parasitic on fruit-infesting Tephritidae (Diptera). Contributions of the American Entomological Institute, Ann Arbor, 30, 1 - 53." type="journal article" year="1997">Wharton 1997</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gahan" authorityYear="1930" box="[344,485,1126,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Opius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis box="[344,485,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Opius bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dark-brown tibiae. In 
<collectingCountry box="[781,852,1126,1151]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, some specimens have dark-brown tibiae and others have yellowish tibiae. These specimens were considered as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wesmael" authorityYear="1835" box="[828,895,1164,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Opius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,895,1164,1187]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Opius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gahan" authorityYear="1930" box="[943,1055,1163,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Opius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
aff. 
<emphasis box="[988,1055,1163,1188]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for about two decades. However, based on geometric morphometry and molecular analyses, it was concluded that specimens with yellowish tibiae actually belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gahan" authorityYear="1930" box="[372,478,1235,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Opius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis box="[372,478,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">O. bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well (
<bibRefCitation author="Marinho, C. F. &amp; Consoli, F. L. &amp; Zucchi, R. A." box="[592,835,1235,1260]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="409 - 419" refId="ref7485" refString="Marinho, C. F., Consoli, F. L. &amp; Zucchi, R. A. (2014) Geometric morphometry and molecular analysis clarified the identity of Opius sp. aff. bellus (Hymenoptera, Braconidae), a fruit fly parasitoid in Brazil. Zootaxa, 3760 (3), 409 - 419. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3760.3.7" type="journal article" year="2014">
Marinho 
<emphasis box="[702,754,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gahan" authorityYear="1930" box="[858,1004,1235,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Opius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis box="[858,1004,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Opius bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite common in several fruit-fly surveys, recorded in 22 Brazilian states, and is predominant in the state 
<collectingRegion box="[974,1092,1271,1295]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Canal D. &amp; N. A &amp; Zucchi, R. A. &amp; Silva, N. M. da &amp; Leonel Junior, F. L." box="[1108,1309,1270,1295]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref6596" refString="Canal D., N. A., Zucchi, R. A., Silva, N. M. da &amp; Leonel Junior, F. L. (1994) Reconocimiento de las especies de parasitoides (Hymenoptera: Braconidae) de moscas de las frutas (Diptera: Tephritidae) en dos municipios del Estado de Amazonas, Brasil. Boletin del Museo de Entomologia de la Universidad del Falle, 2 (1 / 2), 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1994">
Canal 
<emphasis box="[1184,1242,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
1994
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Canal D. &amp; N. A &amp; Zucchi, R. A. &amp; Silva, N. M." box="[1322,1379,1270,1295]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="235 - 246" refId="ref6683" refString="Canal D., N. A., Zucchi, R. A. &amp; Silva, N. M. (1995) Analise faunistica dos parasitoides (Hymenoptera: Braconidae) de Anastrepha spp. (Diptera: Tephritidae) em Manaus e Iranduba, Estado do Amazonas. Acta Amazonica, 25, 235 - 246. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 1809 - 43921995253246" type="journal article" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingRegion box="[151,209,1307,1332]" country="Brazil" name="Piaui" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Piauí</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Araujo, A. A. R. &amp; Silva, P. R. R. &amp; Silva, R. B. Q. &amp; Sousa, E. P. S. &amp; Soares, L. L." box="[228,453,1307,1332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="1739 - 1750" refId="ref6059" refString="Araujo, A. A. R., Silva, P. R. R., Silva, R. B. Q., Sousa, E. P. S. &amp; Soares, L. L. (2014) Moscas-das-frutas (Diptera: Tephritidae) associada a frutiferas nativas de Spondias spp. (Anacardiaceae) e Ximenia americana L. (Olacaceae) e seus parasitoides no estado do Piaui, Brasil. Semina: Ciencias Agrarias, 35 (4), 1739 - 1750. https: // doi. org / 10.5433 / 1679 - 0359.2014 v 35 n 4 p 1739" type="journal article" year="2014">
Araújo 
<emphasis box="[320,382,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vilanova, E. S. &amp; Silva A. F. V. &amp; Martins, J. O. &amp; Bezerra-Silva, G. C. D. &amp; Silva, M. A." box="[469,716,1307,1332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="1" refId="ref9529" refString="Vilanova, E. S., Silva A. F. V., Martins, J. O., Bezerra-Silva, G. C. D. &amp; Silva, M. A. (2016) Diversidade e biogeografia de parasitoides de moscas-das-frutas no Piaui, Brasil. XXIV Congresso Brasileiro de Fruticultura: Fruteiras nativas e sustentabilidade, Sao Luis, Maranhao, Brasil, 2016, 1 CD-ROM." type="journal article" year="2016">
Vilanova 
<emphasis box="[583,644,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Souza, L. &amp; Silva, P. R. R. &amp; Nascimento, M. P. P. &amp; Franca, S. M. &amp; Araujo, A. A. R." box="[732,948,1307,1332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="4" refId="ref9059" refString="Souza, L. S, Silva, P. R. R., Nascimento, M. P. P., Franca, S. M. &amp; Araujo, A. A. R. (2017) Fruit flies (Diptera: Tephritidae) and their parasitoids associated with diferent Hog Plum genotypes in Teresina, Piaui. Revista Brasileira de Agricultura, 39 (4), (e- 725). http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / 0100 - 29452017725" type="journal article" year="2017">
Souza 
<emphasis box="[813,867,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). It parasitizes 19 species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" box="[1301,1429,1307,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Anastrepha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1301,1429,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Anastrepha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including some of economic importance, and 
<taxonomicName box="[663,788,1343,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[663,788,1343,1367]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">C. capitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Zucchi, R. A. &amp; Moraes, R. C. B." box="[847,1110,1342,1367]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" refId="ref9964" refString="Zucchi, R. A. &amp; Moraes, R. C. B. (2008) Fruit flies in Brazil- Anastrepha species their host plants and parasitoids. Updated 16 May 2018. Available from: http: // www. lea. esalq. usp. br / anastrepha / (accessed 23 July 2018)" type="url" year="2008">Zucchi &amp; Moraes 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zucchi, R. A. &amp; Moraes, R. C. B." box="[1122,1183,1343,1367]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" refId="ref10023" refString="Zucchi, R. A. &amp; Moraes, R. C. B. (2012) Fruit flies in Brazil-Hosts and parasitoids of the Mediterranean fruit fly. Updated 18 January 2018. Available from: http: // www. lea. esalq. usp. br / ceratitis / (accessed 23 July 2018)" type="url" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
